-> rough plan
-> project: make a quiz looking like kahoot using python tkinter GUI
-> think of 5 or 10 questions with 4 choices each
-> add buttons, widget label, time library, random library, preferably add the song too
-> create a tuple to insert the questions, and the options and the guesses, and print the user’s score

_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_

-> import tkinter
       -> from tkinter import*
       -> window.mainloop()
-> create a window, resize it, rename the title, change the logo
       -> [SIZE] window.geometry(“{pixel size}”)
       -> [TITLE] window.title(“{title}”)
       -> [IMAGE] Photoimage(file=”filename.png”)
       -> [LOGO] window.iconphoto(True, icon)
       -> [BG COLOR] window.config(background=”color”)
-> add a label to the window, edit the label, insert image to the label
       -> [POSITION] label.pack()
       -> [MANUAL]  label.place(x=0, y=0)
-> add a button widget to the window
       -> button(window, text=”{text}”)
       -> button.pack()
       -> button.config(command={click})
       -> button.congfig(font=({style}, {size}, {bold}))
       -> button.config(bg=”color”)
       -> button.config(image=image)
       -> button.config(compound=”top or bottom”)
       -> [DISABLE] button.config(state=ACTIVE or DISABLED)
       -> label = Label(window, text=count)
       -> label.pack()
       -> label.config(font=”{style}, {size}”)
       -> label.config(text=count)
      -> button.pack()

